The Programme
The Programme considers the history and the archaeology of Ancient Macedonia, covering the region of Macedonia and the
Macedonians from the Mycenaean period until the Roman era.
Programme Structure Schedule
First Semester The MA in the Classical Archaeology and the Ancient History
of Macedonia is a 3-semester full-time programme of study.
It is taught mainly on weekdays over three-hour teaching
▶ The Historical Sources
periods. Each teaching term consists of 13 teaching weeks
▶ Archaeological Sites of Macedonia
followed by a 10-day exam period. The third semester is taken
▶ Historical Geography and Cartography of Ancient Macedonia
up with work on the Master’s dissertation. The programme is
▶ The Prehistoric Macedonia
also available in part-time mode.
▶ The Hellenistic and Roman Periods
▶ Minor Arts (Pottery, Metalworking etc.) Excavation
Second Semester An important part of the students’ education on this MA will
be their participation in a training excavation to be organised
▶ Ancient History of Macedonia by the International Hellenic University within the specific
framework of the MA.
▶ Monumental Art
▶ Coinage and Economy
Guided excursions, international workshops, special lectures
▶ Cults and Beliefs
and team projects by the students will also play a significant
▶ Languages and Dialects in Macedonia
role. The MA in The Classical Archaeology and the Ancient
▶ New Technologies in Archaeology History of Macedonia emphasizes the acquisition of a holistic,
▶ Excavation in-depth grounding in the study of Ancient Macedonia and
its cultural influence, at an institution located at its heart and
next to its archaeological sites.
Study the history,
archaeology and art of
Ancient Macedonia in the
heart of contemporary
Macedonia.
