ANNOUNCEMENT
FOR ADMISSION TO THE ENGLISH-LANGUAGE INTERDEPARTMENTAL
POSTGRADUATE PROGRAM
«AERIAL AUTONOMOUS SYSTEMS»
FOR THE ACADEMIC YEAR 2026-27
The English-language Interdepartmental Postgraduate Program “Autonomous Aerial
Systems” of the Faculty of Engineering at the Aristotle University of Thessaloniki invites
interested candidates to submit applications for admission to the new Interdepartmental
Postgraduate Program (IPP) “Aerial Autonomous Systems” for the academic year 2026–
2027.
The courses of the Interdepartmental Postgraduate Program are delivered entirely
through distance learning methods.
Purpose of the Postgraduate Program
The aim of the Interdepartmental Postgraduate Program is to equip students with
advanced interdisciplinary skills required for the design, performance, optimization,
operational utilization, and assessment of the technical and economic viability of
unmanned vehicle systems. Within this framework, students will acquire specialized
knowledge governing modern autonomous systems in areas characterized by
interdisciplinarity, thereby broadening the scope of the Interdepartmental Postgraduate
Program.
The expected learning outcomes and qualifications of those who successfully complete
the Interdepartmental Postgraduate Program (IPP) are estimated to be:
• The advancement of knowledge and the development of research in the scientific and
technological field of autonomous systems
• Equipping graduates with the necessary knowledge required for their integration into
a demanding, rapidly changing environment with interdisciplinary characteristics, as
dictated by the new conditions prevailing worldwide.
• Providing knowledge to meet the needs of research and teaching in the broad field of
design and construction, control, telecommunications, operational functionality, and
innovative methods of mapping and positioning through the integration of modern
technologies.
• Preparation for doctoral-level studies.
Employment prospects and professional opportunities for graduates are available in
Ministries, Local Government Authorities, public and private organizations, legal entities
under public law, industries, public institutions, media, as well as various Research
Institutes. In addition, graduates acquire the ability to work independently or
collaboratively in research activities—often within the framework of international
research programs—to seek new knowledge and stay updated with the latest scientific
developments, to present and defend their work to others, and, more generally, to
become familiar with research practices.
