The goal of this graduate program is to present, explain and comprehend  the politics, history, international relations, economy and culture of the United States of America.
The program includes two semesters of courses and a summer period when students will write their thesis. The curriculum is developed in consultation with Professors from New York University’s Center for Global Affairs, who also teach in the Program.
The program accepts applications from students who have completed their undergraduate studies prior to the commencement of classes in early October of every academic year.
