---
The MSc «
Advances in Computer Science and Information Systems
» aims to provide specialized knowledge in advanced topics and applications of Information Technology and Telematics, especially in the fields of data management and artificial intelligence, cloud and internet of things technologies and infrastructures and the development of applications in this environment, as well as in the use of information systems in the management of businesses and organizations and digital transformation. Its graduates will be able to meet the needs of public and private institutions, to participate in high-level research and development and to produce new scientific knowledge.
---
Data Science and Algorithms (Big Data Management, Semantic Web and Knowledge Graphs, Data Mining, Statistics and Applications, Computational Theory, Algorithms and Programming Languages)
---
Internet of Everything and Next Generation Networks (Internet of Everything Applications and Services, Intelligent Transport Systems and Autonomous Driving, 6G Technology Networks)
